content:
OmniScripts Select Element

Enable users to select from a dropdown by adding a Select element to your OmniScript. Users can enter text to filter the options. OmniStudio pulls the options from an Apex class and method or from a Salesforce object.

Drag a Select element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
Give the element a label in Field Label.
In Option Source, select the source of the options:
Manual: Manually enter value and label pairs.
Custom: Enter the Apex class and method that returns the options. Use the format ClassName.method.
SObject: Retrieves the picklist values from the Salesforce object and field.

If you select Manual or Custom as an option source, follow these steps:
Click + Add New Option.
Enter the Value and visible Label.
(Optional) Check Use as Default to make the option selected by default.
(Optional) Check Auto Advance to advance the user to the next step when they click this option.

If you select SObject as an Option Source, enter the name of a field on an object in the format SObject.field.

To display options based on the selection of another value, configure Controlling Field Type by selecting Custom or SObject.
In Controlling Field Source, enter an Apex class.
In Controlling Field Element, enter an OmniScript element name.

(Optional) For additional properties, see Common OmniScript Element Properties Definitions.
title: OmniScript Select Element
